title.narrative: CHILD PROTECTION SYSTEMS ENHANCEMENT

description.narrative: By 2021, there will be increased country capacity to promote and ensure justice and systems that enable the prevention and treatment of violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect, which contributes to Climate Change, Disaster Risks And Envionmental Degradation, Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas (Covid), Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid), Violence, Exploitation And Abuse. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, national legislation is implemented to prevent, mitigate and address violence and other childhood abuses and the justice, education, public health, security and other sectors observe children's rights to this protection.

title.narrative: By 2021, there will be increased country capacity to promote and ensure justice and systems that enable the prevention andtreatment of violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect

description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF continued to increase the capacity of countries in the Eastern Caribbean Area to prevent and respond to violence against children with Antigua and Barbuda, Grenada and Barbados approving new child protection and gender-based violence policies, Trinidad and Tobago developing its first national inter-agency child abuse protocol and child protection referral pathways developed in St. Vincent and the Grenadines to support coordination during the emergency. UNICEF continued to support the strengthening of juvenile justice systems across the eastern Caribbean with four countries improving procedures and services ensuring access to child-friendly services for children in contact with the law | Status:On-track | As-of Date:18/01/2022
